SIMPLE: microcosm
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Microcosm
<hw>Mi"cro*cosm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>microcosme</ets>, L. <ets>microcosmus</ets>, fr. Gr.
<grk>mikro`s</grk> small + <grk>ko`smos</grk> the world.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A little world; a miniature universe. Hence (so called
by Paracelsus), a man, as a supposed epitome of the exterior universe or
great world. Opposed to <contr>macrocosm</contr>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A relatively small object or system considered as
representative of a larger system of which it is part, exhibiting many
features of the complete system.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Microcosmical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Microcosmic</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>{
